body:
@srednax @dehoeninger don't agree. browser should be able to handle file if possible. let me explain: i want to write newsletters with images in my owncloud. i can do it with dropbox, because the browser "understands" what file it is opening and, if it is an image, it is opened in the browser.
yes, i knew the &download option, but that is not the behaviour i was looking for.
don't know if what i'm asking for is possible?

@srednax i know. in fact, i thought that you were asking for the same functionality as i am looking for. do the &download link work as you expected in forum.kde.org ?

i was asking for something like https://github.com/owncloud/core/blob/master/core/img/favicon.png?raw=true

what i think this link actually does is that it translates the url into another one, which gives you a direct link to the file. that's exactly what i need to do.

calm down, no need to get angry :-)

the reason why the file is not displayed in the browser and downloaded instead is actually mostly a security decision, the point here is that this would allow stored xss, flash based xss, open redirectors etc...

if you have a look at dropbox you will see that they use a different subdomain (dl.dropbox.com) for such potential insecure content. (which mitigates these attacks, since javascript can't do anything dangerous on www.dropbox.com thanks to same origin policy)

if someone wants to solve this, fine, you would have to check if the mimetype is safe to display. but to be honest, i' m actually absolutely fine with the current approach and you would have to convince us that your solution is secure ;-)

@lukasreschke thanks for the explanation about the security issue, i didn't know that. i had already noticed that dropbox changed the domain when the link was pointing directly to the file. but i didn't know the reason. 
anyway, github also has the possiblity to view the file in the browser, with the option ?raw=true 
is there any possibility of adding / developing this behaviour in owncloud?
in any case, thanks a lot for taking your time answering these posts, it is very useful to me!

@srednax for me it is obvious that what you want is different from what i am saying. sorry if posting my doubts in this thread has lead to misunderstanding. when i read your issue i thought it was the same as mine. i don't understand either what is what you want / need exactly.

@yokinfx:
> anyway, github also has the possiblity to view the file in the browser, with the option ?raw=true 

could you give me an example url? - thx!

@srednax:
sorry, i don't really get your problem, could you please open a new bug report using our issue template (including the "step by step" reproduce)? thx.

@lukasreschke of course... 
https://github.com/owncloud/core/blob/master/core/img/favicon.png?raw=true

@srednax i think that for your purposes, the &download is ok, right? and that you only want to change the default behaviour to &download, or not??? 
if that is what you want, i think you have misunderstood something: &download option is not unsecure. what is unsecure is what i am asking for, which is showing the image or file in the browser 

i think that lukasreschke asks you to open a new issue with your desired behaviour, because it does not relate to the original post int this thread -well, not directly... :-)
